To replicate the user interface shown in your image using React, you'll need to create a layout that includes a header, a main content area with a sidebar, and a video player or image placeholder. Below, I'll guide you through setting up a simple React application that mimics this structure.

### Step 1: Set Up Your React Project

First, create a new React application using Create React App if you haven't already set up a project.

```bash
npx create-react-app video-lecture-ui
cd video-lecture-ui
```

### Step 2: Create Basic Components

You'll need several components to build this UI:

- `Header` for the top area
- `Sidebar` for navigation links like Notes, Transcript, etc.
- `MainContent` for displaying the video and lecture information
- `Footer` if needed, for additional navigation or information

Here’s a basic setup:

#### `Header.js`

```jsx
import React from 'react';

function Header() {
  return (
    <div className="header">
      <h1>Lecture Title</h1>
    </div>
  );
}

export default Header;
```

#### `Sidebar.js`

```jsx
import React from 'react';

function Sidebar() {
  return (
    <div className="sidebar">
      <button>Notes</button>
      <button>Transcript</button>
      <button>Attachments</button>
    </div>
  );
}

export default Sidebar;
```

#### `MainContent.js`

```jsx
import React from 'react';

function MainContent() {
  return (
    <div className="main-content">
      {/* This could be a video player or an image placeholder */}
      <img src="path_to_your_image_or_video_thumbnail" alt="Lecture" />
      <div className="lecture-info">
        <p>You need to know how to program...</p>
        {/* Add more content as needed */}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

export default MainContent;
```

### Step 3: Assemble Components in `App.js`

```jsx
import React from 'react';
import Header from './Header';
import Sidebar from './Sidebar';
import MainContent from './MainContent';
import './App.css'; // Assuming you have some basic CSS

function App() {
  return (
    <div className="app">
      <Header />
      <div className="content">
        <Sidebar />
        <MainContent />
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

### Step 4: Styling with CSS

Add some basic styles in `App.css`:

```css
.app {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

.header {
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  padding: 20px;
  text-align: center;
}

.content {
  display: flex;
  height: 100vh;
}

.sidebar {
  flex: 1;
  background-color: #ddd;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 20px;
}

.main-content {
  flex: 5;
  background-color: #fff;
  padding: 20px;
}

button {
  margin-top: 10px;
}
```

### Step 5: Run Your Application

Now, you can start your application to see the UI:

```bash
npm start
```

