1. Event handling for player input
2. Player movement logic
3. Computer AI movement
4. Piece falling mechanics
5. Drawing the game state
6. Checking for game over conditions
7. Displaying game over statistics
8. Waiting for player input to exit when the game is over

This loop will run continuously until both players have lost and the player chooses to exit the game. It handles all aspects of gameplay, rendering, and end-game scenarios.

